  <h2>India is known for all the foods they have and ingredients that they use in the food. One famous and very hard to make dish is Biryani! Biryani uses a variety of ingredients and spices and one small error can mess it up. It can be made using any non-vegetarian item you want as well such as chicken, fish, shrimp. etc. Here is a video on how to make Chicken Biryani, and here is the finished product!</h2>
 <a href="http://www.twipu.com/La_Coutch"><img align="left"src= "Biryani.jpg" width="500" height="300"></a>
 <p align="right"><iframe width="500" height="300" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/PmqdA05OXuI" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
 <br>
 <br>
 <h2>Another famous Dish in India is Chicken Curry which is a dish that you can find almost anywhere in India. Similar to Biryani Chicken Curry requires mastery in cooking as it needs an exact amount of certain spices or else it will be too spicy or way too bland. </h2> 
  <a href="http://www.kidskunst.info/linked/chicken-rassa-kombdi-rassa-maharashtrian-chicken-curry-636869636b656e.htm"><img align="left"src= "Chicken_Curry.jpg" width="500" height="300"></a>
